<module>
  <title><m>-(e)ach</m> derivational suffix</title>
  <p></p>
  <p><strong>-(e)ach</strong> is a suffix used to create both <a href="?xx=adjectives/derived_adjectives">derived adjectives</a> 
    and masculine <a href="?xx=nouns/derived_common_nouns">derived common nouns</a> from other nouns.</p>
  
  <h5>Adjectives</h5>
  <p>De-nominal adjectives –</p>
  <ul>
    <li><i>beus</i> <en>moral, virtue</en> ⇒ <m>beusach</m> <en>decent, virtuous</en></li>
    <li><i>fìrinn</i> <en>truth</en> ⇒ <m>fìrinneach</m> <en>truthful</en> (cf. <i>fìor</i> <en>true</en>)</li>
    <li><i>mì-bheus</i> <en>immorality</en> ⇒ <m>mì-bheusach</m> <en>immoral, indecorous</en></li>
    <li><i>mì-chiata</i> <en>dislike</en> ⇒ <m>mì-chiatach</m> <en>unseemly, awful</en></li>
    <li><i>mì-chinnt</i> <en>uncertainty</en> ⇒ <m>mì-chinnteach</m> <en>uncertain</en></li>
    <li><i>mì-chliù</i> <en>infamy, disrepute</en> ⇒ <m>mì-chliùiteach</m> <en>disreputable</en></li>
    <li><i>mì-chothrom</i> <en>unfairness</en> ⇒ <m>mì-chothromach</m> <en>unfair, uneven</en></li>
    <li><i>mì-chreideas</i> <en>distrust</en> ⇒ <m>mì-chreideasach</m> <en>distrustful</en></li>
    <li><i>mì-chùram</i> <en>carelessness</en> ⇒ <m>mì-chùramach</m> <en>careless</en></li>
    <li><i>mì-dhealbh</i> <en>deformity</en> ⇒ <m>mì-dhealbhach</m> <en>grotesque, shapeless</en></li>
    <li><i>mì-earbsa</i> <en>misgiving</en> ⇒ <m>mì-earbsach</m> <en>mistrustful</en></li>
    <li><i>mì-fhoighidinn</i> <en>impatience</en> ⇒ <m>mì-fhoighidneach</m> <en>impatient</en></li>
    <li><i>mì-fhortan</i> <en>misfortune</en> ⇒ <m>mì-fhortanach</m> <en>unfortunate</en></li>
    <li><i>sunnd</i> <en>good humour</en> ⇒ <m>sunndach</m> <en>cheerful</en></li>
  </ul>
  <p>[cf. <xref id="Gillies1902" p="151"/>]</p>
  
  <h5>Nouns</h5>
  <p><a href="?xx=nouns/ethnonymic_common_nouns">Ethnonymic common nouns</a> –</p>
  <ul>
    <li><i>Dòmhnall</i> <en>Donald</en> ⇒ <m>Dòmhnallach</m> <en>a MacDonald</en></li>
    <li><i>Camshron</i> <en>Cameron</en> ⇒ <m>Camshronach</m> <en>a Cameron</en></li>
  </ul>
  <p>Collective examples –</p>
  <ul>
    <li><i>giuthas</i> <en>pine</en> ⇒ <m>giùthsach</m> <en>pine forest</en></li>
    <li><i>iubhar</i> <en>yew</en> ⇒ <m>iùbhrach</m> <en>yew grove</en></li>
  </ul>
  <p>[cf. <xref id="Gillies1902" p="151"/>]</p>
  
  
